                <h1>How to Smooth Backgrounds in Photoshop: Easy Guide</h1>
                <p>To smooth the background in Photoshop, first, select the layer you want to edit. Use the 'Select and Mask' feature to create a clean selection around the subject. Once selected, apply a Gaussian Blur filter to the background layer to soften it. Adjust the blur amount to achieve the desired smoothness while preserving your subject's clarity.</p>
